HEADWORD: Armorial
<hw>Ar*mo"ri*al</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>armorial</ets>, fr. <ets>armoiries</ets> arms, coats of arms, for
<ets>armoieries</ets>, fr. OF. <ets>armoier</ets> to paint arms, coats
of arms, fr. <ets>armes</ets>, fr. L. <ets>arma</ets>. See
<er>Arms</er>, <er>Armory</er>.]</ety> <def>Belonging to armor, or to
the heraldic arms or escutcheon of a family.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Figures with <qex>armorial</qex> signs of race and birth.</q>
<rj><qau>Wordsworth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Armorial bearings</b></col>. <cd>See <er>Arms</er>,
4.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

